summaries.full: Despite the feud with Roman, Bill considers launching an expensive marketing campaign for Home Plus. Nicki gives a pair of missionaries the heave-ho; Margene is invited to Pam's church; Ben goes on a road trip with fellow Seminary students; Alby finds novel ways to occupy his time; Barb discovers Nicki's secret; Roman gives his answer to Bill's proposal.

summaries.short: Bill's household gets a lot more crowded; Franklin indulges his bad habits; Roman is surprised by Bill's new offer.
summaries.full: Having been evicted from their temporary lodgings, Franklin, his wives and dog descend on Bill's just in time for Easter--as does Joey, who's looking for a fresh start. Meanwhile, Bill finds himself drowning in lawsuits; Nicki learns she's not alone in debt; Sarah unexpectedly bonds with Lois; and Bill surprises Roman with a final settlement offer.

summaries.short: Bill makes Roman a settlement proposal; Barb bails out Nicki; Lois sees an opportunity for promotion.
summaries.full: Bill heads to Juniper Creek to attend the funeral of his father's first wife Roberta, and to make Roman a settlement proposal he may or may not be able to refuse. Lois sees Roberta's demise as an opportunity to rise to First Wife. Meanwhile, Barb bails Nicki out of a jam at Home Plus, and Ben ponders whether he should follow in his father's footsteps.
